%p <span class="vcard"><a class="url fn" href="http://alexroman.com/">Alex Roman</a></span> did the modelling, texturing, lighting and rendering. He did postproduction, editing and direction. Unbelievably, he also did the musical sequencing, orchestration and mixing.

%p This film is one man&rsquo;s dedication to a vision, the fullest realisation of his talents.

.figure-box.minor
  .figure
    %a{:href => "http://www.flickr.com/photos/lachlanhardy/4262484078/in/set-72157623055201199", :title => "By Lachlan Hardy, on Flickr"}
      %img{:src => "http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4022/4262484078_8d13bc4a5c_m.jpg", :width => "240", :alt => ""}
    %p
      %a{:href => "http://www.flickr.com/photos/lachlanhardy/4262484078/in/set-72157623055201199"} Lachlan Hardy

%p The film starts with classic architectural designs. Panning across shapes, exploring light. It gradually takes on harder subjects, shooting the buildings within their environment. The detail is so well realised that it takes the fantastical to remind us we&rsquo;re watching a representation rather than the actuality.

%p And indeed, as the piece goes on, it introduces tiny elements of the surreal.

